[size=4][b]xlibs: Shared utility library for STALKER Anomaly modding[/b][/size]
by Damian
Latest: 1.2.3

[url=https://github.com/damiansirbu-stalker/xlibs]GitHub[/url]

xlibs is a modder's toolbox covering the full surface of what Anomaly mods typically need - entity queries, squad operations, smart terrain logic, stash manipulation, logging, profiling, event systems, and data structures.

The API design comes from reverse engineering the X-Ray engine and Anomaly internals, cross-referenced with patterns from the best modders in both the European and Russian STALKER modding traditions. Every function wraps engine quirks, guards against nil, and handles edge cases that would otherwise require each mod to solve independently.

Pure Lua where possible. No engine dependency unless necessary. No central loader - the engine auto-loads scripts on first access. Just call xlog.get_logger() or xsquad.find_squads() and it works.

[line]

[size=3][b]Features[/b][/size]

[size=2][b]Entity and World[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]xcreature[/b] - Creature identification, type checks, fluent server object query iterator
[*][b]xsquad[/b] - Squad search, scripted control, release, chase, iteration
[*][b]xsmart[/b] - Smart terrain queries, faction detection, capacity, arrival, conquest
[*][b]xlevel[/b] - Level/map queries, game time, location names, vertex validation
[*][b]xobject[/b] - Server object resolution from any input type, offline item creation
[*][b]xstash[/b] - Stash discovery, looting, filling, item filtering
[*][b]xdata[/b] - Unscriptable NPC/squad tables (traders, mechanics, story characters)
[*][b]xconst[/b] - X-Ray engine sentinel constants (invalid entity ID, invalid level vertex ID)
[/list]

[size=2][b]Data Structures[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]xtable[/b] - Filter, find, reduce, clone, shuffle, sort, binary insert, memoize, locks
[*][b]xttltable[/b] - TTL key-value store and sliding window counter with auto-expiry
[*][b]xmath[/b] - Probability rolls, weighted choice, random sampling, variation
[*][b]xstring[/b] - String interpolation with ${key} placeholders
[/list]

[size=2][b]Diagnostics[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]xlog[/b] - Buffered file logging with session management and rotation
[*][b]xprofiler[/b] - Microsecond code profiling via engine profile_timer
[*][b]xtrace[/b] - Trace ID generation for request tracking across modules
[*][b]xinspect[/b] - Deep table and userdata inspection, engine type identification
[/list]

[size=2][b]Integration[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]xbus[/b] - Pub/sub event bus with pcall-wrapped delivery and diagnostics
[*][b]xevent[/b] - Runtime function hooking for synthetic callbacks
[*][b]xpda[/b] - PDA messages and map markers (squad and entity)
[*][b]xmcm[/b] - MCM config getters and loaders with defaults extraction
[/list]

[line]

[size=3][b]Requirements[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]Anomaly 1.5.3
[*]Modded exes
[/list]

[size=3][b]Install (MO2)[/b][/size]
[list=1]
[*]Install xlibs
[*]Load order does not matter (scripts are auto-loaded by the engine on demand)
[/list]

[size=3][b]Uninstall (MO2)[/b][/size]
Disable or remove in MO2. Any mod depending on xlibs will stop working.

[size=3][b]Configuration[/b][/size]
No configuration needed. xlibs is a passive library loaded on demand by other mods.

[size=3][b]Compatibility[/b][/size]
Pure library. Does not modify any base scripts, does not register callbacks, does not run any background logic. Compatible with everything including GAMMA.

[line]

[size=3][b]Development[/b][/size]
Written against X-Ray Monolith engine source, Demonized exes source code, and Anomaly 1.5.3 unpacked gamedata.
Code patterns and engine usage validated against established work by reputable GAMMA modders (Demonized, Vintar0, RavenAscendant, xcvb).
The code is validated in real time by a multi-stage pipeline: luacheck, selene, tree-sitter AST analysis, contract rules, cross-file dependency resolution, cyclomatic complexity analysis, crash and vulnerability pattern detection, lua54 integration testing with X-Ray engine stubs, gitleaks secret scanning.
Full report in doc/test-report.log.

[size=3][b]Usage and License[/b][/size]
Calling xlibs functions from your mod: this is the intended use. No restrictions, no credit needed.
Using xlibs as a dependency and listing it in your requirements: encouraged.
Modpacks: allowed and encouraged. Keep the readme and license files.
Copying xlibs code into your own mod instead of depending on it: allowed if you credit "xlibs by Damian Sirbu" visibly on your mod page. Copying without credit is a license violation.
Cloning xlibs modules (like the event bus or data structures) into a competing library: not allowed.
Full license in LICENSE file and on GitHub.

[size=3][b]Credits[/b][/size]
